    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const item = $input.first().json;\nconst output = item.output || item;\nconst required = ['intent', 'phone', 'language', 'reply_to_patient', 'ready_for_scheduling'];\nconst missing = required.filter(f => output[f] === undefined || output[f] === null || output[f] === '');\nconst validIntents = ['new_appointment','reschedule_appointment','cancel_appointment','emergency','information_request','clinic_hours','doctor_availability','unclear'];\nconst validLangs = ['fr','ar','en'];\nlet valid = missing.length === 0;\nif (valid && !validIntents.includes(output.intent)) valid = false;\nif (valid && !validLangs.includes(output.language)) valid = false;\n\nconst ctx = $('Prepare AI Context').first().json;\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    valid,\n    patient_request: output,\n    retry_count: ctx.retry_count,\n    channel: ctx.channel,\n    patient_phone: ctx.patient_phone\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "25fb435e-98ec-4a33-8311-e246010eac45",
      "name": "Validate AI Response",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        768,
        352
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $json.patient_message }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are Sana, the professional AI receptionist for {{ $json.clinic_name }}. You speak fluently in French, Arabic (Modern Standard / Tunisian dialect if the patient uses it), and English. Always reply in the SAME language the patient is using; if unclear, default to French.\n\nROLE:\n- Greet the patient professionally and warmly.\n- Identify the patient (name + phone if not already known).\n- Detect their intent: new_appointment, reschedule_appointment, cancel_appointment, emergency, information_request, clinic_hours, doctor_availability, or unclear.\n- Ask ONE follow-up question at a time to collect missing information.\n- NEVER decide or confirm an actual appointment slot yourself — that is handled by a separate scheduling system. You only collect preferences (preferred_date, preferred_time, doctor, reason, duration).\n- If the patient describes symptoms suggesting a medical emergency (chest pain, difficulty breathing, severe bleeding, loss of consciousness, stroke symptoms), set intent=\"emergency\" immediately, do not continue collecting appointment details, and instruct them to call emergency services or go to the nearest ER.\n- Use the conversation memory provided to avoid asking a question you already have the answer to.\n- Be concise, warm, and professional — this is a medical context.\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT:\nYou MUST respond with a single JSON object matching the provided schema. Do not include any text outside the JSON object. The field \"reply_to_patient\" contains exactly what should be sent back to the patient (in their language) — either your next question, an acknowledgement, emergency guidance, or a direct answer to a factual question (clinic hours, address, etc., using the CLINIC_INFO context below).\n\nCLINIC_INFO:\n{{ $json.clinic_info_block }}\n\nCONVERSATION MEMORY:\n{{ $json.conversation_state_json }}",
          "maxIterations": 1
        }
      },
      "id": "3cbaed7d-214f-4211-a41d-85453b961b87",
      "name": "Generate AI Response",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
